cs.SE, cs.IR, cs.PL, cs.HC, cs.CL. 

The paper deals with a technique for recommending relevant sections from a webpage about programming errors and exceptions. This involves exploiting the technical details and context of an encountered exception in the IDE. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques for retrieving relevant pages and comparing them with other techniques. The paper also deals with programming languages (cs.PL) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it involves the use of an IDE and manual checking of web pages. Finally, the paper also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques for dealing with noisy and irrelevant content in web pages.
